.TH "t3_os_link_changed" 9 "t3_os_link_changed" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t3_os_link_changed \- handle link status changes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" t3_os_link_changed
.BI "(struct adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "int port_id "  ","
.BI "int link_stat "  ","
.BI "int speed "  ","
.BI "int duplex "  ","
.BI "int pause "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
the adapter associated with the link change
.IP "port_id" 12
the port index whose limk status has changed
.IP "link_stat" 12
the new status of the link
.IP "speed" 12
the new speed setting
.IP "duplex" 12
the new duplex setting
.IP "pause" 12
the new flow-control setting

This is the OS-dependent handler for link status changes.  The OS
neutral handler takes care of most of the processing for these events,
then calls this handler for any OS-specific processing.
